value.0: This giant wreck drifts aimlessly in a loose orbit of Viscara, a monument to some past battle.

This beacon floats along the jump point of a local hyperlane. Fitted with solar panels, its transmitter constantly broadcasts a short message in multiple languages common to this region of space.

Even without the beacon's warning, your ship's long range sensors can easily detect that the space ahead is not safe. Many worlds war wartorn, active battles between mighty fleets rage on, and debris from many an unlucky spacefarer litters space ahead.

The message is as follows:
"Attention travellers! The space ahead is contested territory. Pirates and worse have greatly diminished the Republic's ability to patrol the hyperlanes and keep them safe for travel and commerce. Should you proceed down this path, rescue may be delayed or impossible if you find yourself overwhelmed. It is recommended that only the most well prepared venture down this hyperlane.

Further, any ships coming or going down this hyperlane are subject to search by Republic authorities. Per Republic Senate GSD-213.45.8, no warrant is needed for this search. Those found to be smuggling on behalf of the Empire will be subject to arrest and prosecution."
